## Setting Type 2: Pavé Band — The Diamond Band Setting for Oval

A pave oval diamond ring combines a solitaire-style head with a pavé diamond band — tiny accent diamonds set flush into the band metal, running along the shank on both sides. The oval diamond engagement ring with pave band is the fastest-growing style in the oval setting category.

**Why the oval diamond pave band works:** The horizontal flow of pavé accent diamonds running along the finger reinforces the oval's elongating direction. A round diamond in a pavé band is just more sparkle. An oval diamond in a pavé band creates directional elongation — the diamond and the band both point the same way, making the finger appear visibly longer.

**Three band styles:**
- **Petite pavé** — small diamonds (~0.01ct each), thin band, center stone dominant
- **Micro-pavé** — ultra-small diamonds, denser spacing, more sparkle per millimeter
- **Full pavé** — larger accent stones, wider coverage, maximum sparkle intensity

