## Setting Type 4: Three-Stone — Oval Center with Side Stone Drama

A three-stone oval ring places two side stones flanking the oval center. The side stone shape determines the entire character of the ring — and for oval diamonds, the side stone pairing matters more than for any other center shape. The oval's elongated axis creates a natural visual line across the ring; side stones either reinforce or undermine that line.

**Pear side stones:** Teardrop-shaped stones pointing outward. The pointed tip extends the ring's visual outline, reinforcing the oval's elongating direction. Pear side stones and oval centers share similar curves — both organic, both elongated. The combination creates the most finger-lengthening three-stone look available.

**Baguette side stones:** Rectangular step-cut stones. Baguettes flank the oval with clean, architectural lines — maximum contrast between the oval's curves and the baguettes' rectangles. The result is an Art Deco aesthetic with high design clarity. The [Tapered Baguette in Platinum at $2,390](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/tapered-baguette-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-194517?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (215 reviews) is the most-reviewed three-stone setting on all of Blue Nile — across every diamond shape.

**Marquise side stones:** Football-shaped stones with pointed ends on both sides. These create the sharpest wing effect — the most dramatic three-stone profile. With an oval center, marquise side stones create a three-pointed visual that is bold and distinctly contemporary.

**Round side stones:** The most forgiving option. Round brilliant side stones work with any center shape and allow the oval center to define the ring's character. The [Marquise Cut Three Stone by JA at $2,170](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/marquise-cut-diamond-three-stone-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315098?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (152 reviews) is the most-reviewed marquise side stone setting.

