**The side stone sizing rule:** For an oval center diamond, side stones should be approximately 40–50% of the center diamond's carat weight each. A 2ct oval pairs well with 0.80–1.00ct total side stone weight (two stones at 0.40–0.50ct each). Under-proportioned side stones look weak against the oval's width; over-proportioned ones steal attention from the center.

